# genesis-spaces.word — the making of the place, told in I's own words. Faithful to sprout.js
# ensureSpaceRoot: first the place root, then heaven, then heaven's nine rooms (my working memory
# surfaced as spaces), then the host's two rooms and the factory's two. Each sentence is ONE word =
# ONE moment = ONE fact (the Spacebar Law); each lays a do:makespace fact on the new space's reel,
# the space's name standing as its id.
#
# Each room is spoken WITH its parent: `I make X in Y.` — the parent nests (parent -> position). The
# COORD is NOT spoken here: an un-placed creation gets a derived spot automatically (with_default_
# placement), so spaces are never hardcoded and every future space gets a position for free. Speak
# `... at x, y.` only to pin a specific spot.
#
# The place root — the story's outermost space, off which every being and tree hangs.
I make the root.
# Heaven — my home room, the dot, where the runtime stands.
I make heaven in root.
# The nine rooms of heaven, in order: my working memory, each surfaced as a space.
I make extensions in heaven.
I make tools in heaven.
I make ables in heaven.
I make operations in heaven.
I make source in heaven.
I make threads in heaven.
I make histories in heaven.
I make host in heaven.
I make factory in heaven.
# The host's two rooms — the HTTP listener and the WebSocket pool.
I make http in host.
I make websocket in host.
# The factory's two rooms — the live stamper lanes and the reel projections.
I make present in factory.
I make past in factory.
